{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 1 shows an example of how our system processes the statement \"Japan has the 2nd highest life expectancy.\"",
    "In the first step, the system focuses on understanding the specifics of the claim.",
    "Frame-semantic parsing (Das et al., 2014) enables the extraction of frames and their frame elements from claims.",
    "By extracting this representation, the system gains a comprehensive understanding of the claim, which is critical for downstream tasks such as evidence retrieval and verification.",
    "For example, in Figure 1, the Occupy Rank frame is evoked, which characterizes the claim in terms of an Item occupying a certain Rank along a Dimension."
  ]
}